column1: If TRUE, the MSCHAPv2 authentication method will not be used.
column3: 如果為TRUE，則不使用MSCHAPv2身份驗證方法。

column1: If TRUE, the PAP authentication method will not be used.
column3: 如果為TRUE，則不使用PAP驗證方法。

column1: If TRUE, MPPE (Microsoft Point-to-Point Encryption) will be required for the PPP session.  If either 64-bit or 128-bit MPPE is not available the session will fail.  Note that MPPE is not used on mobile broadband connections.
column3: 如果為TRUE，則PPP會話將需要MPPE（Microsoft點對點加密）。如果64位或128位MPPE不可用，則會話將失敗。請注意，MPPE不用於移動寬帶連接。

column1: If TRUE, 128-bit MPPE (Microsoft Point-to-Point Encryption) will be required for the PPP session, and the \"require-mppe\" property must also be set to TRUE.  If 128-bit MPPE is not available the session will fail.
column3: 如果為TRUE，則PPP會話將需要128位MPPE（Microsoft點對點加密），並且“require-mppe”屬性也必須設置為TRUE。如果128位MPPE不可用，則會話將失敗。

column1: If given, specifies the parent interface name on which this PPPoE connection should be created.  If this property is not specified, the connection is activated on the interface specified in \"interface-name\" of NMSettingConnection.
column3: 如果給定，則指定應在其上創建此PPPoE連接的父接口名稱。如果未指定此屬性，則會在NMSettingConnection的“interface-name”中指定的接口上激活連接。

column1: Password used to authenticate with the PPPoE service.
column3: 用於通過PPPoE服務進行身份驗證的密碼。

column1: If specified, instruct PPPoE to only initiate sessions with access concentrators that provide the specified service.  For most providers, this should be left blank.  It is only required if there are multiple access concentrators or a specific service is known to be required.
column3: 如果指定，則指示PPPoE僅啟動與提供指定服務的訪問集中器的會話。對於大多數提供商，這應該留空。只有在有多個訪問集中器或已知需要特定服務時才需要它。

column1: Username used to authenticate with the PPPoE service.
column3: 用於通過PPPoE服務進行身份驗證的用戶名。

column1: Whether the proxy configuration is for browser only.
column3: 代理配置是否僅適用於瀏覽器。

column1: Method for proxy configuration, Default is NM_SETTING_PROXY_METHOD_NONE (0)
PAC URL for obtaining PAC file.

Speed to use for communication over the serial port.  Note that this value usually has no effect for mobile broadband modems as they generally ignore speed settings and use the highest available speed.
column3: 通過串行端口進行通信的速度。請注意，此值通常對移動寬帶調製解調器沒有影響，因為它們通常會忽略速度設置並使用最高可用速度。

column1: Byte-width of the serial communication. The 8 in \"8n1\" for example.
column3: 串行通信的字節寬度。例如，“8n1”中的8。

column1: Parity setting of the serial port.
Time to delay between each byte sent to the modem, in microseconds.
column3: 發送到調製解調器的每個字節之間的延遲時間，以微秒為單位。

column1: Number of stop bits for communication on the serial port.  Either 1 or 2. The 1 in \"8n1\" for example.
column3: 串口通信的停止位數。 1或2.例如“8n1”中的1。

column1: Whether to autoprobe virtual functions by a compatible driver. If set to NM_TERNARY_TRUE (1), the kernel will try to bind VFs to a compatible driver and if this succeeds a new network interface will be instantiated for each VF. If set to NM_TERNARY_FALSE (0), VFs will not be claimed and no network interfaces will be created for them. When set to NM_TERNARY_DEFAULT (-1), the global default is used; in case the global default is unspecified it is assumed to be NM_TERNARY_TRUE (1).
column3: 是否通過兼容的驅動程序自動探測虛擬功能。如果設置為NM_TERNARY_TRUE（1），則內核將嘗試將VF綁定到兼容的驅動程序，如果成功，將為每個VF實例化新的網絡接口。如果設置為NM_TERNARY_FALSE（0），則不會聲明VF，也不會為它們創建網絡接口。設置為NM_TERNARY_DEFAULT（-1）時，使用全局默認值;如果未指定全局默認值，則假定它是NM_TERNARY_TRUE（1）。

column1: The JSON configuration for the team network interface.  The property should contain raw JSON configuration data suitable for teamd, because the value is passed directly to teamd. If not specified, the default configuration is used.  See man teamd.conf for the format details.
column3: 團隊網絡接口的JSON配置。該屬性應包含適合teamd的原始JSON配置數據，因為該值直接傳遞給teamd。如果未指定，則使用默認配置。有關格式詳細信息，請參閱man teamd.conf。

column1: Link watchers configuration for the connection: each link watcher is defined by a dictionary, whose keys depend upon the selected link watcher. Available link watchers are 'ethtool', 'nsna_ping' and 'arp_ping' and it is specified in the dictionary with the key 'name'. Available keys are:   ethtool: 'delay-up', 'delay-down', 'init-wait'; nsna_ping: 'init-wait', 'interval', 'missed-max', 'target-host'; arp_ping: all the ones in nsna_ping and 'source-host', 'validate-active', 'validate-inactive', 'send-always'. See teamd.conf man for more details.
column3: 用於連接的鏈接觀察者配置：每個鏈接觀察者由字典定義，其密鑰取決於所選擇的鏈接觀察者。可用的鏈接觀察者是'ethtool'，'nsna_ping'和'arp_ping'，它在字典中用鍵'name'指定。可用的密鑰是：ethtool：'delay-up'，'delay-down'，'init-wait'; nsna_ping：'init-wait'，'interval'，'miss-max'，'target-host'; arp_ping：nsna_ping和'source-host'中的所有內容，'validate-active'，'validate-incative'，'send-always'。有關更多詳細信息，請參閱teamd.conf man。

column1: Corresponds to the teamd runner.name. Permitted values are: \"roundrobin\", \"broadcast\", \"activebackup\", \"loadbalance\", \"lacp\", \"random\".
column3: 對應於 teamd runner.name。允許的值為：\"roundrobin\", \"broadcast\", \"activebackup\", \"loadbalance\", \"lacp\", \"random\"。

column1: The JSON configuration for the team port. The property should contain raw JSON configuration data suitable for teamd, because the value is passed directly to teamd. If not specified, the default configuration is used. See man teamd.conf for the format details.
column3: 團隊端口的JSON配置。該屬性應包含適合teamd的原始JSON配置數據，因為該值直接傳遞給teamd。如果未指定，則使用默認配置。有關格式詳細信息，請參閱man teamd.conf。

column1: Corresponds to the teamd ports.PORTIFNAME.queue_id. When set to -1 means the parameter is skipped from the json config.
column3: 對應於teamd ports.PORTIFNAME.queue_id。設置為-1表示從json配置中跳過該參數。

column1: The group ID which will own the device. If set to NULL everyone will be able to use the device.
column3: 擁有設備的組ID。如果設置為NULL，則每個人都可以使用該設備。

column1: The operating mode of the virtual device. Allowed values are NM_SETTING_TUN_MODE_TUN (1) to create a layer 3 device and NM_SETTING_TUN_MODE_TAP (2) to create an Ethernet-like layer 2 one.
column3: 虛擬設備的操作模式。允許的值是NM_SETTING_TUN_MODE_TUN（1）來創建第3層設備，NM_SETTING_TUN_MODE_TAP（2）來創建類似以太網的第2層。

column1: If the property is set to TRUE, the interface will support multiple file descriptors (queues) to parallelize packet sending or receiving. Otherwise, the interface will only support a single queue.
column3: 如果該屬性設置為TRUE，則接口將支持多個文件描述符（隊列）以並行化數據包發送或接收。否則，接口將僅支持單個隊列。

column1: The user ID which will own the device. If set to NULL everyone will be able to use the device.
column3: 擁有設備的用戶ID。如果設置為NULL，則每個人都可以使用該設備。

column1: If TRUE the interface will prepend a 4 byte header describing the physical interface to the packets.
column3: 如果為TRUE，則接口將在前面添加一個描述數據包物理接口的4字節頭。

column1: If TRUE the IFF_VNET_HDR the tunnel packets will include a virtio network header.
column3: 如果為TRUE，則IFF_VNET_HDR隧道數據包將包含virtio網絡頭。

column1: A dictionary of key/value pairs with user data. This data is ignored by NetworkManager and can be used at the users discretion. The keys only support a strict ascii format, but the values can be arbitrary UTF8 strings up to a certain length.
column3: 包含用戶數據的鍵/值對字典。 NetworkManager會忽略此數據，並可由用戶自行決定使用。鍵只支持嚴格的ascii格式，但值可以是任意UTF8字符串，長度可達一定。

column1: For outgoing packets, a list of mappings from Linux SKB priorities to 802.1p priorities.  The mapping is given in the format \"from:to\" where both \"from\" and \"to\" are unsigned integers, ie \"7:3\".
column3: 對於傳出數據包，從Linux SKB優先級到802.1p優先級的映射列表。映射以“from：to”格式給出，其中“from”和“to”都是無符號整數，即“7：3”。

column1: One or more flags which control the behavior and features of the VLAN interface.  Flags include NM_VLAN_FLAG_REORDER_HEADERS (0x1) (reordering of output packet headers), NM_VLAN_FLAG_GVRP (0x2) (use of the GVRP protocol), and NM_VLAN_FLAG_LOOSE_BINDING (0x4) (loose binding of the interface to its master device's operating state). NM_VLAN_FLAG_MVRP (0x8) (use of the MVRP protocol). The default value of this property is NM_VLAN_FLAG_REORDER_HEADERS, but it used to be 0. To preserve backward compatibility, the default-value in the D-Bus API continues to be 0 and a missing property on D-Bus is still considered as 0.
column3: 一個或多個標誌，用於控制VLAN接口的行為和功能。標誌包括NM_VLAN_FLAG_REORDER_HEADERS（0x1）（輸出包頭的重新排序），NM_VLAN_FLAG_GVRP（0x2）（使用GVRP協議）和NM_VLAN_FLAG_LOOSE_BINDING（0x4）（接口鬆散綁定到其主設備的操作狀態）。 NM_VLAN_FLAG_MVRP（0x8）（使用MVRP協議）。此屬性的默認值為NM_VLAN_FLAG_REORDER_HEADERS，但過去為0.為了保持向後兼容性，D-Bus API中的默認值仍為0，D-Bus上的缺失屬性仍被視為0。

column1: The VLAN identifier that the interface created by this connection should be assigned. The valid range is from 0 to 4094, without the reserved id 4095.
column3: 應分配此連接創建的接口的VLAN標識符。有效範圍為0到4094，沒有保留ID 4095。

column1: For incoming packets, a list of mappings from 802.1p priorities to Linux SKB priorities.  The mapping is given in the format \"from:to\" where both \"from\" and \"to\" are unsigned integers, ie \"7:3\".
column3: 對於傳入數據包，從802.1p優先級到Linux SKB優先級的映射列表。映射以“from：to”格式給出，其中“from”和“to”都是無符號整數，即“7：3”。

column1: If given, specifies the parent interface name or parent connection UUID from which this VLAN interface should be created.  If this property is not specified, the connection must contain an \"802-3-ethernet\" setting with a \"mac-address\" property.
column3: 如果給定，則指定應從中創建此VLAN接口的父接口名稱或父連接UUID。如果未指定此屬性，則連接必須包含具有“mac-address”屬性的“802-3-ethernet”設置。

column1: Dictionary of key/value pairs of VPN plugin specific data.  Both keys and values must be strings.
column3: VPN插件特定數據的鍵/值對字典。鍵和值都必須是字符串。

column1: If the VPN service supports persistence, and this property is TRUE, the VPN will attempt to stay connected across link changes and outages, until explicitly disconnected.
column3: 如果VPN服務支持持久性，並且此屬性為TRUE，則VPN將嘗試在鏈路更改和中斷之間保持連接，直到明確斷開連接。

column1: Dictionary of key/value pairs of VPN plugin specific secrets like passwords or private keys.  Both keys and values must be strings.
column3: VPN插件的鍵/值對字典，特定密碼，如密碼或私鑰。鍵和值都必須是字符串。

column1: D-Bus service name of the VPN plugin that this setting uses to connect to its network.  i.e. org.freedesktop.NetworkManager.vpnc for the vpnc plugin.
column3: 此設置用於連接到其網絡的VPN插件的D-Bus服務名稱。即vpnc插件的org.freedesktop.NetworkManager.vpnc。

column1: Timeout for the VPN service to establish the connection. Some services may take quite a long time to connect. Value of 0 means a default timeout, which is 60 seconds (unless overridden by vpn.timeout in configuration file). Values greater than zero mean timeout in seconds.
column3: VPN服務建立連接的超時時間。某些服務可能需要很長時間才能連接。值0表示默認超時，即60秒（除非在配置文件中被vpn.timeout覆蓋）。大於零的值表示以秒為單位的超時。

column1: If the VPN connection requires a user name for authentication, that name should be provided here.  If the connection is available to more than one user, and the VPN requires each user to supply a different name, then leave this property empty.  If this property is empty, NetworkManager will automatically supply the username of the user which requested the VPN connection.
column3: 如果VPN連接需要用戶名進行身份驗證，則應在此處提供該名稱。如果連接可供多個用戶使用，並且VPN要求每個用戶提供不同的名稱，則將此屬性保留為空。如果此屬性為空，NetworkManager將自動提供請求VPN連接的用戶的用戶名。

column1: Specifies the lifetime in seconds of FDB entries learnt by the kernel.
column3: 指定內核學習的FDB條目的生存期（以秒為單位）。

column1: Specifies the UDP destination port to communicate to the remote VXLAN tunnel endpoint.
column3: 指定與遠程VXLAN隧道端點通信的UDP目標端口。

column1: Specifies the VXLAN Network Identifier (or VXLAN Segment Identifier) to use.
column3: 指定要使用的VXLAN網絡標識符（或VXLAN段標識符）。

column1: Specifies whether netlink LL ADDR miss notifications are generated.
column3: 指定是否生成netlink LL ADDR未命中通知。

column1: Specifies whether netlink IP ADDR miss notifications are generated.
column3: 指定是否生成netlink IP ADDR未命中通知。

column1: Specifies whether unknown source link layer addresses and IP addresses are entered into the VXLAN device forwarding database.
column3: 指定是否將未知的源鏈路層地址和IP地址輸入VXLAN設備轉發數據庫。

column1: Specifies the maximum number of FDB entries. A value of zero means that the kernel will store unlimited entries.
column3: 指定FDB條目的最大數量。值為零意味著內核將存儲無限制的條目。

column1: If given, specifies the source IP address to use in outgoing packets.
column3: 如果給定，則指定要在傳出數據包中使用的源IP地址。

column1: If given, specifies the parent interface name or parent connection UUID.
column3: 如果給定，則指定父接口名稱或父連接UUID。

column1: Specifies whether ARP proxy is turned on.

Specifies the unicast destination IP address to use in outgoing packets when the destination link layer address is not known in the VXLAN device forwarding database, or the multicast IP address to join.
column3: 指定當VXLAN設備轉發數據庫中未知目標鏈路層地址或要加入的多播IP地址時，在傳出數據包中使用的單播目標IP地址。

column1: Specifies whether route short circuit is turned on.
column3: 指定是否打開路由短路。

column1: Specifies the maximum UDP source port to communicate to the remote VXLAN tunnel endpoint.
column3: 指定與遠程VXLAN隧道端點通信的最大UDP源端口。

column1: Specifies the minimum UDP source port to communicate to the remote VXLAN tunnel endpoint.
column3: 指定與遠程VXLAN隧道端點通信的最小UDP源端口。

column1: Specifies the TOS value to use in outgoing packets.
column3: 指定要在傳出數據包中使用的TOS值。

column1: Specifies the time-to-live value to use in outgoing packets.
column3: 指定要在傳出數據包中使用的生存時間值。

column1: Flags indicating which mode of WPS is to be used. There's little point in changing the default setting as NetworkManager will automatically determine the best method to use.
column3: 旗標指示要使用 WPS 的哪種模式。更改預設設定沒什麼意義，因為 NetworkManager 將自動決定要使用的最佳方式。

column1: If specified, this connection will only apply to the WiMAX device whose MAC address matches. This property does not change the MAC address of the device (known as MAC spoofing). Deprecated: 1
column3: 如果指定，則此連接僅適用於MAC地址匹配的WiMAX設備。此屬性不會更改設備的MAC地址（稱為MAC欺騙）。不予批准：1

column1: Network Service Provider (NSP) name of the WiMAX network this connection should use. Deprecated: 1
column3: 此連接應使用的WiMAX網絡的網絡服務提供商（NSP）名稱。不予批准：1

column1: If non-zero, only transmit packets of the specified size or smaller, breaking larger packets up into multiple fragments. If zero a default MTU is used. Note that contrary to wg-quick's MTU setting, this does not take into account the current routes at the time of activation.
column3: 如果非零，則僅傳輸指定大小或更小的數據包，將更大的封包分成多個片段。如果為零，會使用預設的 MTU。注意，與 wg-quick 的 MTU 設定相反，這不會考量啟動時的目前路由。

column1: Flags indicating how to handle the \"private-key\" property.
column3: 旗標指示如何處理「private-key」屬性。

column1: If specified, this connection will only apply to the IEEE 802.15.4 (WPAN) MAC layer device whose permanent MAC address matches.
column3: 如果指定，則此連接僅適用於永久MAC地址匹配的IEEE 802.15.4（WPAN）MAC層設備。

column1: Short IEEE 802.15.4 address to be used within a restricted environment.
column3: 要在受限環境中使用的短IEEE 802.15.4地址。
錯誤：建立 NMClient 物件逾時\n

column1: Error: Could not create NMClient object: %s\n
column3: 錯誤：無法建立 NMClient 物件：%s\n

column1: Wait for NetworkManager startup instead of a connection
column3: 等待 NetworkManager 啟動而不是連線

column1: Exit immediately if NetworkManager is not running or connecting
column3: 若 NetworkManager 沒有在執行或連線中的話，即刻退出

column1: Waits for NetworkManager to finish activating startup network connections.
column3: 等待 NetworkManager 完成啟用開啟網路連線。

column1: Invalid option.  Please use --help to see a list of valid options.
column3: 無效的選項。請使用 --help 來查看可用選項的清單。

column1:
Usage: nmcli agent { COMMAND | help }

COMMAND := { secret | polkit | all }
column3:
用法：nmcli agent { 命令 |help }

命令：= { secret | polkit |all }

column1:
Usage: nmcli agent secret { help }

Runs nmcli as NetworkManager secret agent. When NetworkManager requires
a password it asks registered agents for it. This command keeps nmcli running
and if a password is required asks the user for it.
column3:
用法：nmcli agent secret { help }

運行nmcli作為NetworkManager秘密代理。當NetworkManager需要密碼時，它會向註冊代理詢問密碼。此命令使nmcli保持運行，如果需要密碼則詢問用戶。

column1:
Usage: nmcli agent polkit { help }

Registers nmcli as a polkit action for the user session.
When a polkit daemon requires an authorization, nmcli asks the user and gives
the response back to polkit.
column3:
用法：nmcli agent polkit { help }

將nmcli註冊為用戶會話的polkit操作。
當polkit守護程序需要授權時，nmcli會詢問用戶並
將響應返回給polkit。

column1:
Usage: nmcli agent all { help }

Runs nmcli as both NetworkManager secret and a polkit agent.
column3:
用法：nmcli agent all { help }

運行nmcli作為NetworkManager機密和polkit代理。

column1: nmcli successfully registered as a NetworkManager's secret agent.\n
column3: nmcli成功註冊為NetworkManager的秘密代理。\n
錯誤：祕密代理初始化失敗

column1: nmcli successfully registered as a polkit agent.\n

column3: 錯誤：polkit 代理初始化失敗：%s

column1: Warning: password for '%s' not given in 'passwd-file' and nmcli cannot ask without '--ask' option.\n
column3: 警告：密碼'%s' 未在'passwd-file'中給出，並且nmcli不能在沒有'--ask'選項的情況下詢問。\n

column1: Error: Could not create NMClient object: %s.
column3: 錯誤：無法建立 NMClient 物件：%s。

column1: Error: argument '%s' not understood. Try passing --help instead.
column3: 錯誤：參數'%s' 不明白。嘗試傳遞--help代替。
錯誤：缺少參數。嘗試傳遞--help。
連線（名稱、UUID 或是路徑）：
VPN 連線（名稱、UUID 或是路徑）：
連線（名稱、UUID 或是路徑）：
連線（名稱、UUID、路徑或是 apath）：
VPN 連線（需要身份認證）
VPN 連線（取得 IP 配置）

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection { COMMAND | help }

COMMAND := { show | up | down | add | modify | clone | edit | delete | monitor | reload | load | import | export }

  show [--active] [--order <order spec>]
  show [--active] [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

  up [[id | uuid | path] <ID>] [ifname <ifname>] [ap <BSSID>] [passwd-file <file with passwords>]

  down [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

  add COMMON_OPTIONS TYPE_SPECIFIC_OPTIONS SLAVE_OPTIONS IP_OPTIONS [-- ([+|-]<setting>.<property> <value>)+]

  modify [--temporary] [id | uuid | path] <ID> ([+|-]<setting>.<property> <value>)+

  clone [--temporary] [id | uuid | path ] <ID> <new name>

  edit [id | uuid | path] <ID>
  edit [type <new_con_type>] [con-name <new_con_name>]

  delete [id | uuid | path] <ID>

  monitor [id | uuid | path] <ID> ...

  reload

  load <filename> [ <filename>... ]

  import [--temporary] type <type> file <file to import>

  export [id | uuid | path] <ID> [<output file>]
column3:
用法：nmcli connection { 命令 | help }

命令 := { show | up | down | add | modify | clone | edit | delete | monitor | reload | load | import | export }

  show [--active] [--order <order spec>]
  show [--active] [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

  up [[id | uuid | path] <ID>] [ifname <ifname>] [ap <BSSID>] [passwd-file <file with passwords>]

  down [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

  add COMMON_OPTIONS TYPE_SPECIFIC_OPTIONS SLAVE_OPTIONS IP_OPTIONS [-- ([+|-]<setting>.<property> <value>)+]

  modify [--temporary] [id | uuid | path] <ID> ([+|-]<setting>.<property> <value>)+

  clone [--temporary] [id | uuid | path ] <ID> <new name>

  edit [id | uuid | path] <ID>
  edit [type <new_con_type>] [con-name <new_con_name>]

  delete [id | uuid | path] <ID>

  monitor [id | uuid | path] <ID> ...

  reload

  load <filename> [ <filename>... ]

  import [--temporary] type <type> file <file to import>

  export [id | uuid | path] <ID> [<output file>]

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection show { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [--active] [--order <order spec>]

List in-memory and on-disk connection profiles, some of which may also be
active if a device is using that connection profile. Without a parameter, all
profiles are listed. When --active option is specified, only the active
profiles are shown. --order allows custom connection ordering (see manual page).

ARGUMENTS := [--active] [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

Show details for specified connections. By default, both static configuration
and active connection data are displayed. It is possible to filter the output
using global '--fields' option. Refer to the manual page for more information.
When --active option is specified, only the active profiles are taken into
account. Use global --show-secrets option to reveal associated secrets as well.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection show { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [--active] [--order <order spec>]

列出內存和磁盤上的連接配置文件，如果設備使用該連接配置文件，
其中一些配置文件也可能處於活動狀態。如果沒有參數，則列出所有
配置文件。指定--active選項時，僅顯示活動的配置文件。 --order允
許自定義連接排序（參見手冊頁）。

ARGUMENTS := [--active] [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

顯示指定連接的詳細信息。默認情況下，將顯示靜態配置和活動連接數據。
可以使用全局'--fields'選項過濾輸出。有關更多信息，請參閱手冊頁。如果
指定了--active選項，則僅考慮活動配置文件。使用全局--show-secrets選
項來顯示相關的秘密。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection up { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID> [ifname <ifname>] [ap <BSSID>] [nsp <name>] [passwd-file <file with passwords>]

Activate a connection on a device. The profile to activate is identified by its
name, UUID or D-Bus path.

ARGUMENTS := ifname <ifname> [ap <BSSID>] [nsp <name>] [passwd-file <file with passwords>]

Activate a device with a connection. The connection profile is selected
automatically by NetworkManager.

ifname      - specifies the device to active the connection on
ap          - specifies AP to connect to (only valid for Wi-Fi)
nsp         - specifies NSP to connect to (only valid for WiMAX)
passwd-file - file with password(s) required to activate the connection
column3:
用法：nmcli connection up { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID> [ifname <ifname>] [ap <BSSID>] [nsp <name>] [passwd-file <file with passwords>]

在裝置上啟用連線。要啟用的設定檔藉由名稱、UUID 或 D-Bus 路徑識別。

ARGUMENTS := ifname <ifname> [ap <BSSID>] [nsp <name>] [passwd-file <file with passwords>]

使用連線啟用裝置。NetworkManager 會自動選擇連線設定檔。

ifname      - 指定要啟用連線的裝置
ap          - 指定要連線的 AP（只適用於 Wi-Fi）
nsp         - 指定要連線的 NSP（只適用於 WiMAX）
passwd-file - 具有用於啟用連線的密碼的檔案

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection down { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

Deactivate a connection from a device (without preventing the device from
further auto-activation). The profile to deactivate is identified by its name,
UUID or D-Bus path.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection down { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path | apath] <ID> ...

在裝置上停用連線（不避免裝置自動啟用）。要停用的設定檔藉由名稱、
UUID 或 D-Bus 路徑識別。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection clone { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [--temporary] [id | uuid | path] <ID> <new name>

Clone an existing connection profile. The newly created connection will be
the exact copy of the <ID>, except the uuid property (will be generated) and
id (provided as <new name> argument).
column3:
用法：nmcli connection clone { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [--temporary] [id | uuid | path] <ID> <new name>

克隆現有連接配置文件。新創建的連接將是該文件的精確副本 <ID>，
除了uuid屬性（將生成）和id（提供為 <new name> 參數）。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection edit { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID>

Edit an existing connection profile in an interactive editor.
The profile is identified by its name, UUID or D-Bus path

ARGUMENTS := [type <new connection type>] [con-name <new connection name>]

Add a new connection profile in an interactive editor.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection edit { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID>

在互動式編輯程式編輯已存在的連線設定檔。
設定檔藉由名稱、UUID 或 D-Bus 路徑識別

ARGUMENTS := [type <new connection type>] [con-name <new connection name>]

在互動式編輯程式加入新的連線設定檔。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection monitor { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID> ...

Monitor connection profile activity.
This command prints a line whenever the specified connection changes.
Monitors all connection profiles in case none is specified.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection monitor { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID> ...

監控連線 activity.
這個指令會在指定的連線變更時顯示一列。
如果沒有指定連線，會監控所有連線設定檔。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection reload { help }

Reload all connection files from disk.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection reload { help }

從磁碟重新載入所有連線檔案。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection load { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <filename> [<filename>...]

Load/reload one or more connection files from disk. Use this after manually
editing a connection file to ensure that NetworkManager is aware of its latest
state.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection load { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <filename> [<filename>...]

從磁碟載入/重新載入一個或多個連線檔案。手動編輯連線檔案後請使用這個命令
來確保 NetworkManager 知道最後的狀態。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection import { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [--temporary] type <type> file <file to import>

Import an external/foreign configuration as a NetworkManager connection profile.
The type of the input file is specified by type option.
Only VPN configurations are supported at the moment. The configuration
is imported by NetworkManager VPN plugins.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection import { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [--temporary] type <type> file <file to import>

將外部/外部配置導入為NetworkManager連接配置文件。
輸入文件的類型由type選項指定。
目前僅支持VPN配置。
配置由NetworkManager VPN插件導入。

column1:
Usage: nmcli connection export { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID> [<output file>]

Export a connection. Only VPN connections are supported at the moment.
The data are directed to standard output or to a file if a name is given.
column3:
用法：nmcli connection export { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [id | uuid | path] <ID> [<output file>]

匯出連線。目前只支援 VPN 連線。
資料會導向到標準輸出，如果有指定名稱，會輸出到檔案。
更新 %s 的祕密發生錯誤：%s\n

沒有使用中的連線或裝置

連線已成功啟用（D-Bus 啟用路徑：%s）\n

column1: neither a valid connection nor device given

---[ Main menu ]---
goto     [<setting> | <prop>]        :: go to a setting or property
remove   <setting>[.<prop>] | <prop> :: remove setting or reset property value
set      [<setting>.<prop> <value>]  :: set property value
describe [<setting>.<prop>]          :: describe property
print    [all | <setting>[.<prop>]]  :: print the connection
verify   [all | fix]                 :: verify the connection
save     [persistent|temporary]      :: save the connection
activate [<ifname>] [/<ap>|<nsp>]    :: activate the connection
back                                 :: go one level up (back)
help/?   [<command>]                 :: print this help
nmcli    <conf-option> <value>       :: nmcli configuration
quit                                 :: exit nmcli
column3:
---[ 主選單 ]---
goto     [<setting> | <prop>]        :: 前往某項設定或內容
remove   <setting>[.<prop>] | <prop> :: 移除設定或重設內容值
set      [<setting>.<prop> <value>]  :: 設定內容值
describe [<setting>.<prop>]          :: 描述內容
print    [all]                       :: 列印連線
verify   [all]                       :: 驗證連線
save                                 :: 儲存連線
activate [<ifname>] [/<ap>|<nsp>]    :: 啟用連線
back                                 :: 往後返回一層
help/?   [<command>]                 :: 印出此協助畫面
nmcli    <conf-option> <value>       :: nmcli 配置
quit                                 :: 退出 nmcli

column1:
goto <setting>[.<prop>] | <prop>  :: enter setting/property for editing

This command enters into a setting or property for editing it.

Examples: nmcli> goto connection
          nmcli connection> goto secondaries
          nmcli> goto ipv4.addresses
column3:
goto <setting>[.<prop>] | <prop>  :: 進入設定/內容以進行編輯

這項指令會進入一項設定或內容以讓您針對其進行編輯。

範例：nmcli> goto connection
          nmcli connection> goto secondaries
          nmcli> goto ipv4.addresses

column1:
remove <setting>[.<prop>]  :: remove setting or reset property value

This command removes an entire setting from the connection, or if a property
is given, resets that property to the default value.

Examples: nmcli> remove wifi-sec
          nmcli> remove eth.mtu
column3:
remove <setting>[.<prop>]  :: 移除設定或重設內容值

這項指令會移除連線的所有設定，或是若
提供的乃內容的話，會將內容重設爲預設值。

範例：nmcli> remove wifi-sec
          nmcli> remove eth.mtu

column1:
set [<setting>.<prop> <value>]  :: set property value

This command sets property value.

Example: nmcli> set con.id My connection
column3:
set [<setting>.<prop> <value>]  :: 設置內容值

這項指令會設置內容的值。

範例：nmcli> set con.id My connection

column1:
describe [<setting>.<prop>]  :: describe property

Shows property description. You can consult nm-settings(5) manual page to see all NM settings and properties.
column3:
describe [<setting>.<prop>]  :: 描述內容

顯示內容的描述。您可查看 nm-settings(5) man page，以檢視所有的 NM 設定和內容屬性。

column1:
print [all]  :: print setting or connection values

Shows current property or the whole connection.

Example: nmcli ipv4> print all
column3:
print [all]  :: 印出設定或是連線值

顯示目前的內容或是整個連線。

範例：nmcli ipv4> print all

column1:
verify [all | fix]  :: verify setting or connection validity

Verifies whether the setting or connection is valid and can be saved later.
It indicates invalid values on error. Some errors may be fixed automatically
by 'fix' option.

Examples: nmcli> verify
          nmcli> verify fix
          nmcli bond> verify
column3:
verify [all | fix]  :: 驗證設定或連線是否有效

驗證設定或連線是否有效，並且可在之後進行儲存。它會顯示無效的值或是錯誤。
有些錯誤可能可以藉由「fix」選項修理
範例：nmcli> nmcli> verify
          nmcli> verify fix
          nmcli bond> verify

column1:
save [persistent|temporary]  :: save the connection

Sends the connection profile to NetworkManager that either will save it
persistently, or will only keep it in memory. 'save' without an argument
means 'save persistent'.
Note that once you save the profile persistently those settings are saved
across reboot or restart. Subsequent changes can also be temporary or
persistent, but any temporary changes will not persist across reboot or
restart. If you want to fully remove the persistent connection, the connection
profile must be deleted.
column3:
save [persistent | temporary] :: 儲存連線

將連接配置文件發送到NetworkManager，它將永久保存，或者只保留在
記憶體中。沒有參數的'save'意味著'save persistent'。
請注意，一旦您持久保存配置文件，這些設置將在重新啟動或重新啟動時保存
。後續更改也可以是臨時更改或持久更改，但任何臨時更改都不會在重新引導
或重新啟動時保留。如果要完全刪除持久連接，則必須刪除連接配置文件。

column1:
activate [<ifname>] [/<ap>|<nsp>]  :: activate the connection

Activates the connection.

Available options:
<ifname>    - device the connection will be activated on
/<ap>|<nsp> - AP (Wi-Fi) or NSP (WiMAX) (prepend with / when <ifname> is not specified)
column3:
activate [<ifname>] [/<ap>|<nsp>]  :: 啟用連線

啟用連線。

可用選項：
<ifname>    - 連線將會被啟用於的裝置
  /<ap>|<nsp> - AP（Wi-Fi）或是 NSP（WiMAX）（當未指定 <ifname> 時，以 / 作為前置）

column1: back  :: go to upper menu level\n\n
column3: back  :: 往上返回上一層的選單\n\n

column1: help/? [<command>]  :: help for the nmcli commands\n\n

nmcli [<conf-option> <value>]  :: nmcli configuration

Configures nmcli. The following options are available:
status-line yes | no          [default: no]
save-confirmation yes | no    [default: yes]
show-secrets yes | no         [default: no]
prompt-color <color> | <0-8>  [default: 0]
%s
Examples: nmcli> nmcli status-line yes
          nmcli> nmcli save-confirmation no
          nmcli> nmcli prompt-color 3
column3:
nmcli [<conf-option> <value>]  :: nmcli 配置

配置 nmcli。下列爲可用的選項：
status-line yes | no          [default: no]
save-confirmation yes | no    [default: yes]
show-secrets yes | no         [default: no]
prompt-color <color> | <0-8>  [default: 0]
%s
範例：nmcli> nmcli status-line yes
          nmcli> nmcli save-confirmation no
          nmcli> nmcli prompt-color 3

column1:
quit  :: exit nmcli

This command exits nmcli. When the connection being edited is not saved, the user is asked to confirm the action.
column3:
quit  :: 退出 nmcli

這項指令會退出 nmcli。當被編輯的連線尚未儲存時，使用者會被要求確認動作。

This command adds provided <value> to this property, if the property is of a container type. For single-valued properties the property value is replaced (same as 'set').

column1:
Usage: nmcli device status { help }

Show status for all devices.
By default, the following columns are shown:
 DEVICE     - interface name
 TYPE       - device type
 STATE      - device state
 CONNECTION - connection activated on device (if any)
Displayed columns can be changed using '--fields' global option. 'status' is
the default command, which means 'nmcli device' calls 'nmcli device status'.
column3:
用法：nmcli device status { help }

顯示所有裝置的狀態。
預設情況下，會顯示以下欄位：
 DEVICE     - 介面名稱
 TYPE       - 裝置類型
 STATE      - 裝置狀態
 CONNECTION - 裝置啟用的連線（如果有）
顯示的欄位可以使用「--fields」全域選項變更。「status」是
預設指令，這表示「nmcli device」呼叫「nmcli device status」。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device show { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [<ifname>]

Show details of device(s).
The command lists details for all devices, or for a given device.
column3:
用法：nmcli device show { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [<ifname>]

顯示裝置的詳細資訊。
這個指令列出所有裝置或指定裝置的詳細資訊。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device connect { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <ifname>

Connect the device.
NetworkManager will try to find a suitable connection that will be activated.
It will also consider connections that are not set to auto-connect.
column3:
用法：nmcli device connect { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <ifname>

裝置連線。
NetworkManager 會嘗試找到會被啟用的適合的連線。
它也會考慮沒有設為自動連線的連線。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device disconnect { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <ifname> ...

Disconnect devices.
The command disconnects the device and prevents it from auto-activating
further connections without user/manual intervention.
column3:
用法：nmcli device disconnect { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <ifname> ...

裝置斷線。
這個指令使裝置斷線，並避免它在沒有使用者/手動介入下自動啟用連線。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device delete { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <ifname> ...

Delete the software devices.
The command removes the interfaces. It only works for software devices
(like bonds, bridges, etc.). Hardware devices cannot be deleted by the
command.
column3:
用法：nmcli device delete { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := <ifname> ...

刪除軟體裝置。
這個指令會移除介面。這只適用於軟體裝置（例如 bond、橋接等）。
硬體裝置無法被這個指令刪除。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device monitor { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [<ifname>] ...

Monitor device activity.
This command prints a line whenever the specified devices change state.
Monitors all devices in case no interface is specified.
column3:
用法：nmcli device monitor { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [<ifname>] ...

監控裝置活動。
這個指令會在指定的裝置變更狀態時列出一行。
如果沒有指定介面，會監控所有裝置。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device wifi { ARGUMENTS | help }

Perform operation on Wi-Fi devices.

ARGUMENTS := [list [ifname <ifname>] [bssid <BSSID>] [--rescan yes|no|auto]]

List available Wi-Fi access points. The 'ifname' and 'bssid' options can be
used to list APs for a particular interface, or with a specific BSSID. The
--rescan flag tells whether a new Wi-Fi scan should be triggered.

ARGUMENTS := connect <(B)SSID> [password <password>] [wep-key-type key|phrase] [ifname <ifname>]
                     [bssid <BSSID>] [name <name>] [private yes|no] [hidden yes|no]

Connect to a Wi-Fi network specified by SSID or BSSID. The command finds a
matching connection or creates one and then activates it on a device. This
is a command-line counterpart of clicking an SSID in a GUI client. If a
connection for the network already exists, it is possible to bring up the
existing profile as follows: nmcli con up id <name>. Note that only open,
WEP and WPA-PSK networks are supported if no previous connection exists.
It is also assumed that IP configuration is obtained via DHCP.

ARGUMENTS := hotspot [ifname <ifname>] [con-name <name>] [ssid <SSID>]
                     [band a|bg] [channel <channel>] [password <password>]

Create a Wi-Fi hotspot. Use 'connection down' or 'device disconnect'
to stop the hotspot.
Parameters of the hotspot can be influenced by the optional parameters:
ifname - Wi-Fi device to use
con-name - name of the created hotspot connection profile
ssid - SSID of the hotspot
band - Wi-Fi band to use
channel - Wi-Fi channel to use
password - password to use for the hotspot

ARGUMENTS := rescan [ifname <ifname>] [[ssid <SSID to scan>] ...]

Request that NetworkManager immediately re-scan for available access points.
NetworkManager scans Wi-Fi networks periodically, but in some cases it might
be useful to start scanning manually. 'ssid' allows scanning for a specific
SSID, which is useful for APs with hidden SSIDs. More 'ssid' parameters can be
given. Note that this command does not show the APs,
use 'nmcli device wifi list' for that.
column3:
用法：nmcli device wifi { ARGUMENTS | help }

在Wi-Fi設備上執行操作。

ARGUMENTS := [list [ifname <ifname>] [bssid <BSSID>] [--rescan yes|no|auto]]

列出可用的 Wi-Fi 熱點。「ifname」和「bssid」選項可用於列出特定接口的AP
或特定的BSSID。「--rescan」旗標表示是否要觸發新的 Wi-Fi 掃描。

ARGUMENTS := connect <(B)SSID> [password <password>] [wep-key-type key|phrase] [ifname <ifname>]
                     [bssid <BSSID>] [name <name>] [private yes|no] [hidden yes|no]

連接到SSID或BSSID指定的Wi-Fi網絡。該命令創建一個新連接，然後
在設備上激活它。這是在GUI客戶端中單擊SSID的命令行對應物。該
命令始終創建新連接，因此它主要用於連接到新的Wi-Fi網絡。如果已
存在網絡連接，則最好按如下方式顯示現有配置文件：
nmcli con up id <name>。請注意，目前僅支持開放，WEP和WPA-PSK
網絡。還假設通過DHCP獲得IP配置。

ARGUMENTS := hotspot [ifname <ifname>] [con-name <name>] [ssid <SSID>]
                     [band a|bg] [channel <channel>] [password <password>]

創建一個Wi-Fi熱點。使用「connection down」或「device disconnect」
來停止熱點。
熱點的參數可能受可選參數的影響：
ifname - 要使用的Wi-Fi設備
con-name - 創建的熱點連接配置文件的名稱
ssid - 熱點的SSID 
band - 要使用的 Wi-Fi band
channel - 要使用的 Wi-Fi 頻道
password - 用於熱點的密碼

ARGUMENTS := rescan [ifname <ifname>] [[ssid <SSID to scan>] ...]

請求NetworkManager立即重新掃描可用的熱點。 NetworkManager定期
掃描Wi-Fi網絡，但在某些情況下，手動開始掃描可能很有用。 'ssid'允許
掃描特定的SSID，這對於具有隱藏SSID的AP非常有用。可以給出更多'ssid'
參數。請注意，此命令不顯示AP，請使用“nmcli device wifi list”。

column1:
Usage: nmcli device lldp { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [list [ifname <ifname>]]

List neighboring devices discovered through LLDP. The 'ifname' option can be
used to list neighbors for a particular interface.

column1:
Usage: nmcli general hostname { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [<hostname>]

Get or change persistent system hostname.
With no arguments, this prints currently configured hostname. When you pass
a hostname, NetworkManager will set it as the new persistent system hostname.
column3:
用法：nmcli general hostname { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [<hostname>]

獲得或變更持久系統主機名稱。
如果沒有參數，這會顯示目前配置的主機名稱。當您傳遞主機名稱，
NetworkManager 會將它設為新的持久系統主機名稱。

column3:
用法：nmcli networking on { help }

打開網路。

column1:
Usage: nmcli networking off { help }

Switch networking off.
column3:
用法：nmcli networking off { help }

column1:
Usage: nmcli networking connectivity { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [check]

Get network connectivity state.
The optional 'check' argument makes NetworkManager re-check the connectivity.
column3:
用法：nmcli networking connectivity { ARGUMENTS | help }

ARGUMENTS := [check]

獲取網路連線狀態。
選填的「check」引數使 NetworkManager 重新檢查連線能力。

column1:

監視 NetworkManager 的更改。

column1:
Usage: nmcli [OPTIONS] OBJECT { COMMAND | help }

OPTIONS
  -a, --ask                                ask for missing parameters
  -c, --colors auto|yes|no                 whether to use colors in output
  -e, --escape yes|no                      escape columns separators in values
  -f, --fields <field,...>|all|common      specify fields to output
  -g, --get-values <field,...>|all|common  shortcut for -m tabular -t -f
  -h, --help                               print this help
  -m, --mode tabular|multiline             output mode
  -o, --overview                           overview mode
  -p, --pretty                             pretty output
  -s, --show-secrets                       allow displaying passwords
  -t, --terse                              terse output
  -v, --version                            show program version
  -w, --wait <seconds>                     set timeout waiting for finishing operations

OBJECT
  g[eneral]       NetworkManager's general status and operations
  n[etworking]    overall networking control
  r[adio]         NetworkManager radio switches
  c[onnection]    NetworkManager's connections
  d[evice]        devices managed by NetworkManager
  a[gent]         NetworkManager secret agent or polkit agent
  m[onitor]       monitor NetworkManager changes
column3:
用法：nmcli [OPTIONS] OBJECT { COMMAND | help }

OPTIONS
  -a, --ask                                詢問遺失的引數
  -c, --colors auto|yes|no                 是否在輸出中使用顏色
  -e, --escape yes|no                      在值中跳脫欄位分隔符
  -f, --fields <field,...>|all|common      指定要輸出的欄位
  -g, --get-values <field,...>|all|common  -m tabular -t -f 的捷徑
  -h, --help                               顯示這個說明
  -m, --mode tabular|multiline             輸出模式
  -o, --overview                           概述模式
  -p, --pretty                             美化輸出
  -s, --show-secrets                       允許顯示密碼
  -t, --terse                              簡潔輸出
  -v, --version                            顯示程式版本
  -w, --wait <seconds>                     設定完成操作的等待逾時

OBJECT
  g[eneral]       NetworkManager 的一般狀態和操作
  n[etworking]    整體網路控制
  r[adio]         NetworkManager radio 開關
  c[onnection]    NetworkManager 的連線
  d[evice]        NetworkManager 管理的裝置
  a[gent]         NetworkManager 秘密代理或 polkit 代理
  m[onitor]       監控 NetworkManager 變更

column1: Accerciser is an interactive Python accessibility explorer for the GNOME desktop. It uses AT-SPI to inspect and control widgets, allowing you to check if an application is providing correct information to assistive technologies and automated test frameworks.

If “true”, Dconf Editor tries at launch to navigate to the path described in the “saved-view” key.

column1: A path to restore the last view
If the “restore-view” key is set to “true”, Dconf Editor tries at launch to navigate to this path.
column3: 如果「restore-view」設定鍵設定為「true」，Dconf 編輯器會在執行時嘗試跳至這個路徑。

column1: If “true”, Dconf Editor opens a popup when launched reminding the user to be careful.
column3: 如果設定為「true」，Dconf 編輯器在提醒使用者注意時會開啟彈出視窗。

column1: A flag to enable small rows for keys list
column3: 啟用設定鍵列表較小尺寸列表的旗標

column1: If “true”, the keys list use smaller rows.
column3: 如果設定為「true」，設定鍵列表會使用較小的列。

column1: Change the behaviour of a key value change request
column3: 改變設定鍵數值變更要求的行為

column1: The “unsafe” value is discouraged: for keys that have a non-special-cased type, it updates the key value each time something changes in the entry, so including intermediate states. The “safe” value asks for confirmation in these cases, but allows instant changes for booleans and nullable booleans, enums and flags. The “always-confirm-implicit” and “always-confirm-explicit” values always asks for confirmation, but the first applies the change if you change path whereas the second dismiss it. The “always-delay” value adds each change in delay mode, allowing to apply multiple keys at once.
column3: 不建議使用「unsafe」數值：具有 non-special-cased 類型的設定鍵，它會在每次項目中有某些變更時更新數值，因此包含即時的狀態。「safe」數值在那些情況下會詢問以取得確認，但允許布林值與可空布林值、枚舉與旗標的即時變更。「always-confirm-implicit」與「always-confirm-explicit」數值永遠都會要求確認，但如果您改變路徑，首先會套用變更，接著解除它。「always-delay」數值會以延遲模式加入每個變更，允許一次套用多個設定鍵。

column1: A flag to sort keys list case-sensitively
column3: 設定鍵列表是否以區分大小寫方式排序的旗標

column1: GSettings doesn’t allow keys to use upper-case in their names, but installation paths of schemas can. If “true”, the keys list is sorted case-sensitively, with in usual order upper-case folders first.
column3: GSettings 不允許設定鍵在它們的名字使用大寫，但是安裝路徑的基模可以。如果為「true」，設定鍵列表會以區分大小寫的方式排序，以一般的順序來說大寫資料夾會在前。
使用「返回」和「前往」滑鼠按鈕活動

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for “Forward” and “Back”, this key will determine if any action is taken inside of a browser window when either is pressed.
column3: 此設定鍵用於支援「往前」和「往後」按鈕的滑鼠，其將決定哪個按鈕會觸發瀏覽視窗中的「上一頁」指令。

column1: Mouse button to activate the “Back” command in browser window
column3: 用來觸發瀏覽視窗中「上一頁」指令的滑鼠按鈕

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for “Forward” and “Back”, this key will set which button activates the “Back” command in a browser window. Possible values range between 6 and 14.
column3: 用於使用者的滑鼠有「往前」和「往後」按鈕時，這個設定鍵會決定哪個按鈕會觸發瀏覽視窗中的「上一頁」指令。可能的數值範圍在 6 到 14 之間。

column1: Mouse button to activate the “Forward” command in browser window
column3: 用來觸發瀏覽視窗中「下一頁」指令的滑鼠按鈕

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for “Forward” and “Back”, this key will set which button activates the “Forward” command in a browser window. Possible values range between 6 and 14.
column3: 用於使用者的滑鼠有「往前」和「往後」按鈕時，這個設定鍵會決定哪個按鈕會觸發瀏覽視窗中的「下一頁」指令。可能的數值範圍在 6 到 14 之間。

column1: A flag to check for added or removed schemas
column3: 一個檢查增加或移除基模的旗幟

column1: Dconf Editor can monitor if schemas are added or removed from the multiple possible locations. That’s done by checking every three seconds if the schemas list has changed. As this way to do is suboptimal, this function can be disabled by setting this flag to “false”. Note that this option will be removed when a better way to do things is found.
column3: Dconf Editor 可以從多個可能位置監控增加與移除的基模。這是透過每隔三秒檢查基模列表是否變更而達到的。如果你覺得這種達成的方法不太好，可以將這個旗幟設定至「false」以停用此功能。注意：這個選項將會在找到更好的方法之後移除掉。
啟用可重定向基模映射裝置

column1: Mapping of paths to manually associated schemas
column3: 將位置映射到手動對應的基模

column1: A flag for skipping unnecessary subfolders
column3: 跳過非必要子資料夾的旗幟

column1: When a folder only contains one subfolder and no keys, Dconf Editor can jump to that subfolder directly. This flag enables that behaviour.
column3: 當資料夾只包含一個子資料夾且沒有任何設定鍵，Dconf 編輯器可以直接跳轉到該子資料夾，此旗幟啟用此行為。

column1: Contains all paths bookmarked by the user as an array of strings.
column3: 包含使用者以字串陣列標記書籤的所有路徑。

column1: A flag to enable small rows for bookmarks list
column3: 用來啟用書籤列表較小尺寸列表的旗標

column1: If “true”, the bookmarks list use smaller rows.
column3: 如果設定為「true」，書籤列表會使用較小的列。

column1: Booleans can only take two values, “true” or “false”.
column3: 布林數只能是兩種數值，「true」或「false」。

column1: GSettings allows nullable types, that are similar to other types but could take a “nothing” value. A nullable boolean can only take three values, “true”, “false” and “nothing”.
column3: GSettings 允許使用可以為 null 的類型，與其他類型相似，但可以接受「nothing」數值。可空布林數只能為三種數值，「true」、「false」和「nothing」。

column1: A byte value is an integer between 0 and 255. It may be used to pass around characters.
column3: 位元組數值為介於 0 到 255 之間的整數。它可以用於傳遞字元。

column1: The bytestring type is commonly used to pass around strings that may not be valid utf8. In that case, the convention is that the nul terminator character should be included as the last character in the array.
column3: 位元組字串類型通常用來傳遞可能不符 utf8 規範的字串。在這種情況下，依慣例是空結束字元應該包含於陣列成為最後一個字元。

column1: This is the type of an array of bytestrings. The bytestring type is commonly used to pass around strings that may not be valid utf8.
column3: 這是位元組字串陣列的類型。 位元組字串類型通常用來傳遞可能不符 utf8 規範的字串。

column1: The handle type is a 32-bit signed integer value that is, by convention, used as an index into an array of file descriptors that are sent alongside a D-Bus message. If you are not interacting with D-Bus, then there is no reason to make use of this type.
column3: handle 類型是 32 位元有號整數值，依慣例用於隨 D-Bus 訊息一併傳送的檔案描述陣列的索引。如果您不與 D-Bus 互動，則沒有理由使用到這個類型。

column1: An object path is used to identify D-Bus objects at a given destination on the bus. If you are not interacting with D-Bus, then there is no reason to make use of this type.
column3: 用來識別在指定目的匯流排上 D-Bus 物件的路徑。如果您不與 D-Bus 互動，則沒有理由使用到這個類型。

column1: A D-Bus object path array, type ‘ao’
column3: D-Bus 物件路徑陣列，類型「ao」

column1: An object path array could contain any number of object paths (including none: “[]”). If you are not interacting with D-Bus, then there is no reason to make use of this type.
column3: 可以包含任意物件路徑數量的物件路徑陣列 (包含空陣列：「[]」)。如果您不與 D-Bus 互動，則沒有理由使用到這個類型。

column1: A D-Bus signature is a string used as type signature for a D-Bus method or message. If you are not interacting with D-Bus, then there is no reason to make use of this type.
column3: D-Bus 簽名檔是一種字串，用於 D-Bus 方法或訊息的類型簽署。如果您不與 D-Bus 互動，則沒有理由使用到這個類型。

column1: A double value could represent any real number.
column3: 一個雙精度值可以表示任何實數。

column1: Enumerations could be done either with the “enum” attribute, or with a “choices” tag.
column3: 列舉可以使用「enum」屬性或「choices」標籤完成。

column1: Flags could be set by the “enum” attribute.
A 16-bit signed integer. See also the “integer-16-unsigned” key.
column3: 16 位元有號整數。另請參閱「integer-16-unsigned」設定鍵。

column1: A 16-bit unsigned integer. See also the “integer-16-signed” key.
column3: 16 位元無號整數。另請參閱「integer-16-signed」設定鍵。

column1: A 32-bit signed integer. See also the “integer-32-unsigned” key.
column3: 32 位元有號整數。另請參閱「integer-32-unsigned」設定鍵。

column1: A 32-bit unsigned integer. See also the “integer-32-signed” key.
column3: 32 位元無號整數。另請參閱「integer-32-signed」設定鍵。

column1: A 64-bit signed integer. See also the “integer-64-unsigned” key.
column3: 64 位元有號整數。另請參閱「integer-64-unsigned」設定鍵。

column1: A 64-bit unsigned integer. See also the “integer-64-signed” key.
column3: 64 位元無號整數。另請參閱「integer-64-signed」設定鍵。

column1: Every numeral setting (integers and unsigned integers of every type, plus doubles) could be limited to a custom range of values. For example, this integer could only take a value between -2 and 10.
column3: 每個位數的設定值 (每個類型的整數和無符號的整數，加上雙數) 可限制為自訂的數值範圍。例如，此整數只能使用 -2 到 10 之間的一數值。

column1: Dconf Editor lets you edit any settings type supported by GSettings, falling back on a string entry when it doesn’t have a better way to do. Here is a tuple of two 32-bit signed integers.
column3: Dconf 編輯器讓您可以編輯任何 GSettings 支援的設定值類型，當它沒有更好的方案時則回退到字串項目。這裡有兩個 32 位元有號整數元組。

column1: The string type could accept any utf8 string. Note that an empty string “''” is not the same as NULL (nothing); see also the “string-nullable” key.
column3: 字串類型可以接受任何 utf8 字串。請注意空字串「''」不是 NULL (空值)；另請參閱的「string-nullable」設定鍵。

column1: A string array contains any number of strings of whatever length. It may be an empty array, “[]”.
column3: 一個字串陣列，包含任意數量的任何長度字串。它可能是一個空陣列，「[]」。

column1: GSettings allows nullable types, that are similar to other types but could take a “nothing” value. A nullable string can take any string as value, including the empty string “''”, or can be NULL (nothing).
column3: GSettings 允許可以為 null 的類型，類似于其他類型，但可以為「空」值。可以為 null 的字串可以是任何字串值，包括空字串「''」，或可以為 NULL (空值)。

column1: An enumeration could contain only one item, but that’s probably an error. Dconf Editor warns you in that case.
column3: 枚舉可以只包含一個項目，但這可能是一個錯誤。在這種情況下，Dconf 編輯器會警告您。

column1: A range could limit an integer key to only allow one value, but that’s probably an error. Dconf Editor warns you in that case.
column3: 範圍可以限制整數設定鍵僅允許一個數值，但這可能是一個錯誤。在這種情況下，Dconf 編輯器會警告您。

column1: The empty tuple, type and value “()”
There’s an empty tuple type (called sometimes “triv”) that is a tuple with no content, and can only take “()” as value.
column3: 有個空元組類型 (有時稱為「triv」) 是一個沒有內容的位元組，只能將「{}」作為值。

column1: An usual boolean value, defined by a relocatable schema.
column3: 一個通常為布林值的值，由可重定向基模定義。

column1: A 32-bit signed integer, defined by a relocatable schema.
column3: 32 位元有號整數，由可重定向基模定義。

column3: 來自 Conflict1 的未衝突普通設定鍵

column1: This key is a test for multiple schemas in the same path with conflicting keys. Non-conflicting keys should have no issues.
column3: 此設定鍵是用於多個基模、且在相同位置的衝突測試設定鍵。未衝突的設定鍵應該沒有任何問題。

column1: Conflicting key defaulting to “1” that should give an error
column3: 應該對預設值為「1」的衝突設定鍵給出錯誤

column1: This key is a test for multiple schemas in the same path with conflicting keys. It shouldn’t be editable as a key mapped to the same path has a different default value.
column3: 此設定鍵是用於多個基模、且在相同位置的衝突測試設定鍵。其不應該可被編輯，且映射到同樣位置的設定鍵可能包含不同的預設值。

column1: Conflicting key with no range that should give an error
column3: 應該對沒有範圍的衝突設定鍵給出錯誤

column1: This key is a test for multiple schemas in the same path with conflicting keys. It shouldn’t be editable as a key mapped to the same path has a different range.
column3: 此設定鍵是用於多個基模、且在相同位置的衝突測試設定鍵。其不應該可被編輯，且映射到同樣位置的設定鍵可能包含不同的範圍。

column1: A (simple) string conflicting key that should give a error
column3: 應該對 (簡單的) 衝突字串設定鍵給出錯誤

column1: This key is a test for multiple schemas in the same path with conflicting keys. It shouldn’t be editable as a key mapped to the same path has a different type.
column3: 此設定鍵是用於多個基模、且在相同位置的衝突測試設定鍵。其不應該可被編輯，且映射到同樣位置的設定鍵可能包含不同的類型。

column1: Conflicting key from Conflict1 that should give a warning
column3: 應該對來自 Conflict1 的衝突設定鍵給出警告

column1: This key is a test for multiple schemas in the same path with conflicting keys. It can be edited, since the types are compatible, but it is still an issue.
column3: 此設定鍵是用於多個基模、且在相同位置的衝突測試設定鍵。其可編輯，這些類型皆相容，但可能仍有些問題。

column1: A normal non-conflicting key from Conflict2
column3: 來自 Conflict2 的未衝突普通設定鍵

column1: Conflicting key defaulting to “2” that should give an error
column3: 應該對預設值為「2」的衝突設定鍵給出錯誤

column1: Conflicting key with range 0~5 that should give an error
column3: 應該對 0~5 範圍的衝突設定鍵給出錯誤

column1: A nullable-string conflicting key that should give an error
column3: 應該對類型為「可為空字串」的衝突設定鍵給出錯誤

column1: Conflicting key from Conflict2 that should give a warning
column3: 應該對來自 Conflict2 的衝突設定鍵給出警告

column1: A developer tool for browsing and searching API documentation

column1: Devhelp is a developer tool for browsing and searching API documentation. It provides an easy way to navigate through libraries and to search by function, struct, or macro.
column3: Devhelp 是個瀏覽與搜尋 API 文件的開發者工具。它提供簡單的方式來瀏覽函式庫，依函式、結構或巨集搜尋。

column1: The documentation must be installed locally, so an internet connection is not needed to use Devhelp.
column3: 此文件必須於本機安裝，所以使用 Devhelp 不需要網路連線。

column1: Devhelp works natively with GTK-Doc, so the GTK and GNOME libraries are well supported. But other development platforms can be supported as well, as long as the API documentation is available in HTML and a *.devhelp2 index file is generated.
column3: Devhelp 原生與 GTK-Doc 運作，所以 GTK 與 GNOME 函式庫得到了良好的支援。而其他的開發平台同樣也能取得很好的支援，只需要讓 API 文件支援 HTML 並建立 *.devhelp2 索引檔案。

column1: Devhelp integrates with other applications such as Glade, Builder or Anjuta, and plugins are available for different text editors (gedit, Vim, Emacs, Geany, …).
column3: Devhelp 整合了其他的應用程式，像是 Glade、Anjuta 或 Geany，且它的附加元件支援各種不同的文字編輯器（gedit、Vim、Emacs、Geany 等等）。

column1: The Eye of GNOME is the official image viewer for the GNOME desktop. It integrates with the GTK+ look and feel of GNOME, and supports many image formats for viewing single images or images in a collection.
column3: 《GNOME 之眼》是 GNOME 桌面的官方影像檢視器。它整合了 GNOME 的 GTK+ 外觀與感覺，並支援許多影像格式，適合檢視單張影像或收藏圖集中的影像。

column1: The Eye of GNOME also allows to view the images in a fullscreen slideshow mode or set an image as the desktop wallpaper. It reads the camera tags to automatically rotate your images in the correct portrait or landscape orientation.
column3: 《GNOME 之眼》也允許以全螢幕投影片模式檢視影像或是將影像設定為桌面的桌布。它會讀取數位相機的標籤自動將您的影像旋轉到正確的直式或橫式方向。

column1: The color that is used to fill the area behind the image. If the use-background-color key is not set, the color is determined by the active GTK+ theme instead.

column1: Whether the image should be interpolated on zoom-out. This leads to better quality but is somewhat slower than non-interpolated images.
column3: 當縮放影像時是否使用內插法處理。這樣品質會較佳，但顯示時會比不使用內插法的來得慢。

column1: Whether the image should be extrapolated on zoom-in. This leads to blurry quality and is somewhat slower than non-extrapolated images.
column3: 當縮放影像時是否使用外推法處理。這樣會造成品質變模糊，但顯示時會比不使用外推法的來得慢。

column1: Determines how transparency should be indicated. Valid values are CHECK_PATTERN, COLOR and NONE. If COLOR is chosen, then the trans-color key determines the color value used.
column3: 決定表示透明的方式。有效的值為「CHECK_PATTERN」、「COLOR」及「NONE」。如果選取 COLOR，則以 trans-color 設定鍵來決定使用哪種顏色。

column1: Whether the scroll wheel should be used for zooming.
column3: 是否使用滑鼠滾輪來做縮放動作。

column1: The multiplier to be applied when using the mouse scroll wheel for zooming. This value defines the zooming step used for each scroll event. For example, 0.05 results in a 5% zoom increment for each scroll event and 1.00 result in a 100% zoom increment.
column3: 使用滑鼠滾輪縮放時的倍數。這個數值定義每次滾輪事件的縮放級數。舉例來說，0.05 代表每次滾輪事件會以 5% 縮放，而 1.00 代表每次滾輪事件會以 100% 縮放。

column1: If the transparency key has the value COLOR, then this key determines the color which is used for indicating transparency.
column3: 如果表示透明的設定鍵的值是‘COLOR’，這個設定鍵會決定哪一種顏色會用來表示透明。

column1: If this is active, the color set by the background-color key will be used to fill the area behind the image. If it is not set, the current GTK+ theme will determine the fill color.

column1: List of the default search engines. It is an array in which each search engine is described by a name, an address, and a bang (shortcut).
column3: 預設搜尋引擎的列表。它是一個陣列，其中每個搜尋引擎是以名稱、 位址和 bang (捷徑) 順序描述。
啟用 Google 搜尋建議

column1: Whether to show Google Search Suggestion in url entry popdown.
column3: 是否在網址列項目下拉式選單中顯示 Google 搜尋建議。

column1: Force new windows to be opened in tabs
column3: 強制新視窗在分頁中開啟

column1: Force new window requests to be opened in tabs instead of using a new window.
column3: 強制開新視窗的要求在分頁中開啟而不是在新視窗中。

column1: Whether to automatically restore the last session
column3: 是否自動還原上次工作階段

column1: Defines how the session will be restored during startup. Allowed values are “always” (the previous state of the application is always restored), “crashed” (the session is only restored if the application crashes) and “never” (the homepage is always shown).
column3: 定義啟動時工作階段要如何還原。允許的數值有「always」(應用程式的前一個狀態永遠會還原)、「crashed」(工作階段只有在應用程式當機時還原) 和「never」(永遠只顯示首頁)。

column1: Whether to delay loading of tabs that are not immediately visible on session restore
column3: 是否延遲載入在工作階段還原時無法立即顯示的分頁

column1: When this option is set to true, tabs will not start loading until the user switches to them, upon session restore.
column3: 當這個選項設定為 true，分頁在工作階段還原時只會在使用者切換到它們時才開始載入。

column1: List of URLs with content filtering rules in JSON format to be used by the ad blocker.
column3: 廣告阻擋器使用的內容過濾規則網址列表，採 JSON 格式。

column1: Whether to ask for setting browser as default
column3: 是否詢問將瀏覽器設為預設

column1: When this option is set to true, browser will ask for being default if it is not already set.
column3: 當這個選項設定為 true 時，瀏覽器會在其尚未設為預設瀏覽器時提出詢問。

column1: When this option is set to true, browser will always start in incognito mode
column3: 當這個選項設定為 true 時，瀏覽器總是會以隱密模式啟動

column1: Selection (bitmask) which clear data items should be active by default. 1 = Cookies, 2 = HTTP disk cache, 4 = Local storage data, 8 = Offline web application cache, 16 = IndexDB databases, 32 = WebSQL databases, 64 = Plugins data, 128 = HSTS policies cache, 256 = Intelligent Tracking Prevention data.
column3: 選擇區域 (位元遮罩)是否預設使用清除資料項目。1 = Cookies，2 = HTTP 磁碟快取，4 = 本地端儲存區資料，8 = 離線網頁應用程式快取，16 = IndexDB 資料庫，32 = WebSQL 資料庫，64 = 外掛程式資料，128 = HSTS 政策快取，256 = 智慧追蹤防護資料。

column1: Expand tabs size to fill the available space on the tabs bar.
column3: 擴展分頁大小以填滿分頁列上的可用空間。

column1: If enabled the tabs will expand to use the entire available space in the tabs bar. This setting is ignored in Pantheon desktop.
column3: 如果啟用，會擴展分頁大小以填滿分頁列上的整個可用空間。這個設定在 Pantheon 桌面中會被忽略。

column1: The visibility policy for the tabs bar.

Controls when the tabs bar is shown. Possible values are “always” (the tabs bar is always shown), “more-than-one” (the tabs bar is only shown if there’s two or more tabs) and “never” (the tabs bar is never shown). This setting is ignored in Pantheon desktop, and “always” value is used.
column3: 控制分頁列何時顯示。可用的值有「always」(永遠顯示分頁列)、「more-than-one」(如果有兩個以上分頁才顯示分頁列) 和「never」(永遠不顯示分頁列)。這個設定在 Pantheon 桌面中會被忽略，直接使用「always」值。

column1: Keep window open when closing last tab
column3: 關閉最後一個分頁仍保持視窗開啟

column1: If enabled application window is kept open when closing the last tab.
column3: 如果啟用，則應用程式視窗在關閉最後一個分頁後仍保持開啟。

column3: 選擇閱讀器模式中文章的主要內文樣式。可用的值有「sans」(無襯線) 和「serif」(襯線)。

column1: Selects the style of colors for articles displayed in reader mode. Possible values are “light” (dark text on light background) and “dark” (light text on dark background).
column3: 選取閱讀器模式中文章的顯示色彩樣式。可用的值有「light」（暗文字亮背景）和「dark」（亮文字暗背景）。
使用 GNOME 字型設定值。

column1: A value to be used to override serif desktop font when use-gnome-fonts is set.
column3: 當設定「use-gnome-fonts」時用來覆蓋 serif 桌面字型的數值。

column1: A value to be used to override monospace desktop font when use-gnome-fonts is set.
column3: 當設定「use-gnome-fonts」時用來覆蓋 monospace 桌面字型的數值。

column3: 使用自訂的 CSS 檔案來修改網站自己的 CSS。

column3: 使用自訂 JS 檔案修改網站。

column3: 對任何在可編輯區域中輸入的文字進行拼字檢查。

column3: 預設編碼。可接受的數值為 WebKitGTK 所能瞭解的值。

column1: Preferred languages. Array of locale codes or “system” to use current locale.
column3: 偏好的語言。可以是地區代碼的陣列或「system」使用目前的地區設定。

column1: Allow sites to open new windows using JavaScript (if JavaScript is enabled).
column3: 允許網站使用 JavaScript 開啟新視窗 (如果啟用 JavaScript)。

column1: String that will be used as user agent, to identify the browser to the web servers.
column3: 用作使用者代理的字串，讓網頁伺服器辨認瀏覽器時使用。

column1: Whether to block the embedded advertisements that web pages might want to show.
column3: 是否阻擋內嵌於網頁可能顯示的廣告。

column1: Whether to store and prefill passwords in websites.
column3: 是否儲存並預先填寫網站密碼。
啟用針對特定網站的奇技淫巧

column1: Enable quirks to make specific websites work better. You might want to disable this setting if debugging a specific issue.
column3: 啟用奇技淫巧來讓特定網站更順利表現。如果您需要對特定問題除錯，或許會想要停用此設定。

column1: Whether to enable safe browsing. Safe browsing operates via Google Safe Browsing API v4.
column3: 是否要啟用安全瀏覽。安全瀏覽透過 Google Safe Browsing API v4 進行操作。

column1: Whether to enable Intelligent Tracking Prevention.
column3: 是否要啟用智慧追蹤預防。

column1: Allow websites to store local website data
column3: 允許網站儲存本機的網站資料

column1: Whether to allow websites to store cookies, local storage data, and IndexedDB databases. Disabling this will break many websites.
column3: 是否要允許網站儲存 Cookie、本機儲存資料、IndexedDB 資料庫等。停用此功能會影響許多網站運作。

column1: Default zoom level for new pages
column3: 新網頁的預設縮放倍率

column1: Whether to automatically search the web when something that does not look like a URL is entered in the address bar. If this setting is disabled, everything will be loaded as a URL unless a search engine is explicitly selected from the dropdown menu.
column3: 當輸入於位址列中的內容看起來不像網址時，是否要自動搜尋網路。若停用此設定，則任何輸入皆以網址載入，除非使用者有特別從下拉選單明確選取搜尋引擎。

column1: Whether to enable mouse gestures. Mouse gestures are based on Opera’s behaviour and are activated using the middle mouse button + gesture.
column3: 是否要啟用滑鼠手勢。滑鼠手勢根據 Opera 瀏覽器行為設計，請使用滑鼠中鍵 + 手勢繪製來啟用功能。

column1: Keep track of last upload directory
Keep track of last download directory

Whether to enable hardware acceleration. Possible values are “on-demand”, “always”, and “never”. Hardware acceleration may be required to achieve acceptable performance on embedded devices, but increases memory usage requirements and could expose severe hardware-specific graphics driver bugs. When the policy is “on-demand”, hardware acceleration will be used only when required to display 3D transforms.
column3: 是否啟用硬體加速。可用的值有「on-demand」(根據要求)、「always」(總是開啟)、「never」(永遠不要)。嵌入式裝置可能需要硬體加速才能達到可以接受的效能，但是會增加記憶體的使用量需求，而且可能暴露在特定硬體的圖形顯示驅動程式重大臭蟲的風險中。當政策選擇「on-demand」時，硬體加速只會在顯示 3D 變換時的要求下使用。

column1: Whether to present a directory chooser dialog for every download.
column3: 是否每次下載時都要提出目錄選擇器對話盒。

column3: 是否要自動切換至新開啟的分頁。

column1: Whether to enable WebExtensions. WebExtensions is a cross-browser system for extensions.
column3: 是否啟用 WebExtensions。WebExtensions 是跨瀏覽器系統的擴充套件。

column1: Indicates which WebExtensions are set to active.

column3: 網頁應用程式的附加連結

column1: The list of URLs that should be opened by the web application
column3: 應該以網頁應用程式開啟的 URL 列表

column3: 是否在 WebApp 中顯示導覽按鈕。

column3: 如果啟用，則應用程式會在關閉視窗後仍繼續在背景中執行。

column1: If enabled, application cannot be edited or removed.
column3: 如果啟用，應用程式就不能被編輯或移除。

column1: The path of the folder where to download files to; or “Downloads” to use the default downloads folder, or “Desktop” to use the desktop folder.
column3: 放置下載的檔案的資料夾路徑；或是「Downloads」代表預設的下載目錄，或「Desktop」使用桌面資料夾。

column1: The position to use for a new window that is not restored from a previous session.
column3: 不是從前一個工作階段還原的新視窗要使用的位置。

column1: The size to use for a new window that is not restored from a previous session.
column3: 不是從前一個工作階段還原的新視窗要使用的大小。

column1: Whether a new window that is not restored from a previous session should be initially maximized.
column3: 當新視窗不是從前一個工作階段還原時是否應初始為最大化視窗。
停用下一頁與上一頁按鈕

column1: If set to “true”, forward and back buttons are disabled, preventing users from accessing immediate browser history
column3: 若設為「true」時，下一頁與上一頁按鈕會停用，阻止使用者存取即刻的瀏覽器歷史

column3: 自訂的 Firefox Sync 代符伺服器 URL。

column3: 自訂的 Firefox Sync 帳號伺服器 URL。

column3: 連結到 Firefox 帳號的電子郵件用來與 Mozilla 伺服器同步資料。

column3: 目前裝置的同步裝置名稱。

column1: TRUE if Ephy collections should be synced with Firefox collections, FALSE otherwise.
column3: 若 Ephiphany 的收藏集應該和 Firefox 收藏集同步則為 TRUE，否則 FALSE。

column3: 若書籤集應該同步則為 TRUE，否則 FALSE。

column3: 若書籤集需要首次同步則為 TRUE，否則 FALSE。

column3: 若開啟分頁集應該同步則為 TRUE，否則 FALSE。

column1: The timestamp at which last open tabs sync was made.
column3: 上次開啟分頁同步的時間戳記。

column1: Decision to apply when microphone permission is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機要求麥克風的存取權時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to access the user’s microphone. The “undecided” default means the browser needs to ask the user for permission, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to automatically make the decision upon request.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有使用者麥克風的存取權。預設值「undecided」代表瀏覽器需要詢問使用者以獲得授權，而「allow」與「deny」會在收到要求時自動決定。

column1: Decision to apply when geolocation permission is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機要求地理位置存取權時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to access the user’s location. The “undecided” default means the browser needs to ask the user for permission, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to automatically make the decision upon request.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有使用者地理位置的存取權。預設值「undecided」代表瀏覽器需要詢問使用者以獲得授權，而「allow」與「deny」會在收到要求時自動決定。

column1: Decision to apply when notification permission is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機要求通知許可權時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to show notifications. The “undecided” default means the browser needs to ask the user for permission, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to automatically make the decision upon request.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有顯示通知的許可權。預設值「undecided」代表瀏覽器需要詢問使用者以獲得授權，而「allow」與「deny」會在收到要求時自動決定。

column1: Decision to apply when save password permission is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機要求密碼儲存許可權時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to save passwords. The “undecided” default means the browser needs to ask the user for permission, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to automatically make the decision upon request.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有儲存密碼的許可權。預設值「undecided」代表瀏覽器需要詢問使用者以獲得授權，而「allow」與「deny」會在收到要求時自動決定。

column1: Decision to apply when webcam permission is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機要求網路攝影機存取權時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to access the user’s webcam. The “undecided” default means the browser needs to ask the user for permission, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to automatically make the decision upon request.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有使用者網路攝影機的存取權。預設值「undecided」代表瀏覽器需要詢問使用者以獲得授權，而「allow」與「deny」會在收到要求時自動決定。

column1: Decision to apply when advertisement permission is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機要求廣告許可權時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to allow advertisements. The “undecided” default means the browser global setting is used, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to automatically make the decision upon request.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有廣告的許可權。預設值「undecided」代表使用瀏覽器全域設定，而「allow」與「deny」則會在收到要求時給予主機對應的決定。

column1: Decision to apply when an autoplay policy is requested for this host
column3: 這個主機詢問自動播放政策時所套用的決定

column1: This option is used to save whether a given host has been given permission to autoplay. The “undecided” default means to allow autoplay of muted media, while “allow” and “deny” tell it to allow / deny all requests to autoplay media respectively.
column3: 這個選項是用來儲存指定的主機是否有自動播放的許可權。預設值「undecided」代表允許以靜音自動播放媒體，而「allow」或「deny」則會在收到自動播放媒體要求時對應告知主機允許 / 拒絕。

column1: A simple, clean, beautiful view of the web

column3: 您可以點按頁面選單中的 安裝網站為網頁應用程式…來加入您喜愛的網站。

column1: You are currently browsing incognito. Pages viewed in this mode will not show up in your browsing history and all stored information will be cleared when you close the window. Files you download will be kept.

column1: It will not hide your activity from your employer if you are at work. Your internet service provider, your government, other governments, the websites that you visit, and advertisers on these websites may still be tracking you.
column3: 如果您在工作場所，隱密模式並無法對您的老闆隱藏您的活動蹤跡。您採用的網際網路服務供應商、您的政府、或是您造訪的網站以及這些網站的廣告主仍然可能追蹤您。

column1: This key was deprecated in version 3.10 and should no longer be used. Use “week-start-day-name” instead.

column1: The most recently used version of Evolution, expressed as “major.minor.micro”. This is used for data and settings migration from older to newer versions.
column3: 最近使用的 Evolution 版本，表示法為「major.minor.micro」。這是用於從舊版本的資料和設定值轉換到新版本時。

column3: 這個數值可以是空字串，代表要使用系統圖片資料夾，通常設定在 ~/Pictures。這個資料夾也會在路徑指向不存在的資料夾時使用

column1: Draw spelling error indicators on words as you type.

column3: 辨認文字中的表情符號並取代成影像或萬國碼字元。
使用萬國碼字元表情符號。

column3: 在回覆郵件時要插入的文字，說明郵件的原作者

column1: Put the cursor at the bottom of replies
Users get all up in arms over where the cursor should go when replying to a message. This determines whether the cursor is placed at the top of the message or the bottom.
column3: 使用者在回覆郵件時希望游標停在何處。這會決定游標放置在郵件的頂端或底部。

column3: 是否預設在每封郵件加入讀信回條的要求。
預設傳送 HTML 郵件
預設傳送 HTML 郵件。

column3: 張貼到新聞群組時顯示「回覆」欄位

column1: Digitally sign replies when the original message is signed
column3: 當原始郵件已簽名時也對回信數位簽名

column1: Automatically enable PGP or S/MIME signatures when replying to a message which is also PGP or S/MIME signed.
column3: 當回覆以 PGP 或 S/MIME 簽署的郵件時自動啟用 PGP 或 S/MIME 簽署。

column1: Encode filenames in an Outlook/GMail way
column3: 將檔案名稱編碼為 Outlook/GMail 形式

column1: Encode filenames in the mail headers same as Outlook or GMail do, to let them display correctly filenames with UTF-8 letters sent by Evolution, because they do not follow the RFC 2231, but use the incorrect RFC 2047 standard.
column3: 將郵件標頭中的檔案名稱編碼為 Outlook 或 GMail 的形式，好讓它們能正確顯示由 Evolution 寄出的 UTF-8 字元檔案名稱，因為它們並未遵循 RFC 2231 規範，而用了不正確的 RFC 2047 標準。

column1: Always save messages to Outbox folder when sending, to let a user choose when the messages should be sent.
column3: 傳送時永遠將郵件儲存至寄件匣，讓使用者選擇郵件何時可送出。

column1: Include signature in new messages only
column3: 只在新郵件中包含簽名檔

column1: Include selected signature only for new messages, but have no signature added for Replies or Forwards.
column3: 只在新郵件中包含選定的簽名檔，回信或轉寄則不使用簽名檔。

column1: Put personalized signatures at the top of replies
column3: 將個人化簽名檔置於回信頂端

column1: Users get all up in arms over where their signature should go when replying to a message. This determines whether the signature is placed at the top of the message or the bottom.
column3: 使用者在回覆郵件時希望他們簽名檔放在何處。這會決定簽名檔放置在郵件的頂端或底部。
無法加入簽名檔分隔符號

column1: Set to TRUE in case you do not want to add signature delimiter before your signature when composing a mail.
column3: 設為 TRUE 表示在您撰寫郵件時不想在簽名檔前加入簽名檔分隔符。

column1: Keep original message signature in replies
column3: 在回信中保留原始郵件簽名檔

column1: When set to TRUE, keep original message signature in replies, otherwise strip the signature and everything below it when replying to the message.
column3: 如果設定為「TRUE」，會在回信中保留原始郵件簽名檔；否則會在回覆郵件時省略簽名檔以及其後的任何文字。

column1: Some mailing lists set a Reply-To: header to trick users into sending replies to the list, even when they ask Evolution to make a private reply. Setting this option to TRUE will attempt to ignore such Reply-To: headers, so that Evolution will do as you ask it. If you use the private reply action, it will reply privately, while if you use the “Reply to List” action it will do that. It works by comparing the Reply-To: header with a List-Post: header, if there is one.
column3: 有些通信論壇會設定 Reply-To: 標頭來誤導使用者傳送回覆的信件到論壇上，即使使用者已要求 Evolution 進行私人回覆也一樣。將這個選項設為 TRUE 會嘗試忽略 Reply-To: 標頭，因此 Evolution 就能依您所要求的行動。如果您使用私人回覆動作，它就會進行回信給個人的動作；而如果您使用「回覆到論壇」動作，它也會照做。它的運作方式是比對 Reply-To: 標頭和 List-Post: 標頭，如果有的話。

column1: Comma-separated list of localized “Re” abbreviations to skip in a subject text when replying to a message, as an addition to the standard “Re” prefix. An example is “SV,AV”.
column3: 當回信時在主旨文字中要略過的本地化「Re」縮寫列表 (逗號分隔)，做為標準「Re」的前綴。例如「SV,AV」。

column1: A list of localized “Re” separators, used to skip in a subject text when replying to a message, as an addition to the standard “:” and the Unicode “︰” separators.
column3: 當回信時在主旨文字中要略過的本地化「Re」分隔字元縮寫列表，一般標準為「:」與萬國碼「︰」分隔字元。
在郵件主旨中使用本地化的 “Fwd”/“Re”

column1: When set to true, uses localized “Fwd”/“Re” in message Subject on reply and forward as provided by current locale translation, otherwise uses unlocalized version.
column3: 如果設定為「true」，會在回信或轉寄的郵件主旨中使用由目前地區翻譯提供的本地化 “Fwd”/“Re”；否則會使用未本地化的版本。

column1: Will autowrap lines after given number of characters.
column3: 在指定字元數後自動進行文字換列。

column1: Number of To and CC recipients to ask “prompt-on-many-to-cc-recips” from
column3: 詢問「prompt-on-many-to-cc-recips」的收件者與副本數目

column1: When to ask, when the number of To and CC recipients reaches this value.
column3: 當收件者與副本數目達到這個數值時，是否要詢問。

column1: Whether to always show Sign and Encrypt buttons on the toolbar
column3: 是否在工具列中顯示簽署與加密按鈕

column3: 如果設定為「true」，PGP 或 S/MIME 的簽署與加密按鈕會永遠顯示在編輯器的工具列上。否則它們只會在被使用時才顯示。
回信中的引文是否換行

column1: If set to “true” quoted text in replies will be wrapped.
column3: 如果設定為「true」回信中的引文會自動換列。
純文字貼上為預先格式化

column3: 設定時，貼至編輯器內文的純文字會成為預先格式化的段落。未設定時，會將它貼成一般段落。

column1: Convert UTC time in reply credits to local time

column1: Whether the time in reply credits should be converted to local time when it’s in UTC in the message.
column3: 是否在回信時將郵件中的 UTC 時刻轉換為本地時刻。

column3: 當回覆郵件時，將它標示為已回覆，同時標記為已閱讀。

column3: 設定為「false」以阻擋 Content-Disposition: inline 附件的顯示。

column3: 拖放操作時儲存的檔案格式

column3: 啟用 HTML 郵件中的動畫影像。許多使用者認為動畫影像很煩人，因而偏好以靜態影像代替。

column1: Enable to use a similar message list view settings for all folders.
column3: 啟用此選項會讓所有的資料夾使用類似的郵件列表檢視設定值。

在郵件「預覽」中標示引用。

column1: Enable caret mode, so that you can see a cursor when reading mail.
column3: 啟用插入號模式，如此您可以在閱讀郵件時看到游標。

column3: 用於顯示郵件的預設字元集

column1: Default charset in which to display messages.
column3: 用於顯示郵件的預設字元集。

column3: 自動透過 HTTP 載入 HTML 郵件的影像

column3: 顯示關於缺少的遠端內容的通知

column3: 當郵件預覽顯示一封郵件需要下載遠端內容，而使用者或網站不允許下載時，在預覽窗格上顯示關於它的通知。

column1: Show all the headers when viewing a messages.
List of headers to show when viewing a message.
column3: 檢視郵件時顯示的檔頭列表。

column1: Each header is represented as a pair: the header name, and a boolean indicating whether the header is enabled. Disabled headers are not shown when viewing a message, but are still listed in Preferences.
column3: 每個檔頭都以配對方式呈現：檔頭的名稱，及一個布林值表示此檔頭是否啟用。停用的檔頭在檢視郵件時不會顯示，但仍會列在偏好設定中。

column1: Allow searching also at libravatar.org for photo of the sender.
column3: 也允許在 libravatar.org 搜尋寄件者的相片。

column3: 在指定的時限過後，標示成已閱讀

column1: Mark as Seen after specified timeout.
column3: 在指定的時限過後，標示成已閱讀。

column1: Mark as Seen always after specified timeout
column3: 在指定的時限過後永遠標示成已閱讀

column1: If set to true, the selected message will be set as unread after the timeout also after the folder change.
column3: 如果設定為 true，選取的郵件會在逾時時間或改變資料夾時設定為未讀。

column1: Show junk messages in the message-list

column1: Show junk messages (with a red strike-through) in the message-list.
column3: 在郵件列表中顯示垃圾的郵件 (加上刪除號)
啟用未符合搜尋資料夾

column1: Enable Unmatched search folder within Search Folders. It does nothing if Search Folders are disabled.
column3: 啟用搜尋資料夾中的未符合搜尋資料夾。如果搜尋資料夾停用則不會有任何動作。

column1: Hides the per-folder preview and removes the selection
column3: 隱藏各資料夾預覽並移除選取區

column1: This key is read only once and reset to “false” after read. This unselects the mail in the list and removes the preview for that folder.
column3: 這個鍵值只能讀取一次，並會在讀取後設為「false」。這樣會取消在列表中對該郵件的選取並移除對該資料夾的預覽。

column1: Whether message headers are collapsed in the user interface
column3: 郵件標題在使用者介面中是否摺疊

column1: The layout style determines where to place the preview pane in relation to the message list. “0” (Classic View) places the preview pane below the message list. “1” (Vertical View) places the preview pane next to the message list.

column1: The variable width font for mail display.
column3: 用於顯示郵件的變動寬度字型。

column1: The terminal font for mail display.
column3: 用於顯示郵件的終端機字型。

column1: Use custom fonts for displaying mail.
column3: 使用自訂字型來顯示郵件。

column1: Compress display of addresses in TO/CC/BCC
column3: 壓縮在 TO/CC/BCC 中位址的顯示方式
